---
title: Pairing Flow
---
sequenceDiagram
    participant H as Host (Windows)
    participant B as BlueZ/bluetoothd
    participant A as Agent (btk_server)
    participant S as L2CAP Sockets

    Note over H,S: 1. Discovery
    H->>H: Scan for devices
    H->>B: Inquiry
    B-->>H: EIR: name=Logitech_K380, UUIDs=(HID, Audio, ...)

    Note over H,S: 2. SDP Query (synchronous with pairing)
    H->>B: L2CAP Connect (PSM 1)
    B-->>H: Accept
    H->>B: SDP ServiceSearch
    B-->>H: 17 service records
    H->>B: SDP AttributeRequest (HID record)
    B-->>H: HID SDP attributes

    Note over H,S: 3. IO Capability Exchange
    H->>B: IO Capability Request<br/>(DisplayYesNo, MITM required)
    B->>A: RequestConfirmation()
    A-->>B: auto-confirm
    B->>A: RequestPasskey()
    A-->>B: 0
    B-->>H: IO Capability Response<br/>(DisplayOnly, no MITM)

    Note over H,S: 4. SSP - Just Works
    H->>B: User Confirmation Request (passkey)
    B->>A: auto-confirm (Just Works)
    B-->>H: User Confirmation Reply
    H->>B: Simple Pairing Complete

    Note over H,S: 5. HID Connection
    H->>B: L2CAP Connect (PSM 17 - HID Control)
    S-->>B: Already listening
    B-->>H: Route to S
    S-->>H: HIDP handshake

    H->>B: L2CAP Connect (PSM 19 - HID Interrupt)
    S-->>B: Already listening
    B-->>H: Route to S
    S-->>H: Ready for input reports
